# EDPA CW Heuristics вЂ” single-source signal weights
#
# CW is computed in detect_contributors.py from these signal weights;
# the engine consumes the resulting per-item-normalized cw values
# directly, without any further role mapping or multi-signal
# aggregation logic of its own.
#
# Mathematics:
#   contribution_score[P, item] = ОЈ signal_weight Г— signal_fired(P, item)
#   cw[P, item]                 = contribution_score[P, item]
#                                 / ОЈ_persons contribution_score[*, item]
#   в†’ ОЈ_persons cw[*, item] = 1.0   (per-item invariant)
#
# Calibrate with `/edpa:calibrate` after collecting в‰Ґ20 ground-truth
# CW records. Monte Carlo over the 5 signal weights, then Nelder-Mead
# refinement around the best candidates. Lower MAD vs. ground truth
# indicates a better calibration.

# Schema version for this heuristics file (independent of methodology version).
schema_version: "1.0"

# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# EVIDENCE SIGNAL WEIGHTS
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
#
# Each weight controls how much that evidence type contributes to a
# person's contribution_score on an item. Higher weight = more
# influence. The values below are reasonable defaults derived from
# the v1.0 Monte Carlo simulation; calibration will tune them against
# real ground truth.
#
# Manual /contribute directives (`manual:*` signal types) carry the
# user-supplied `weight:X` value verbatim вЂ” they're not re-weighted by
# this table. Multiple /contribute lines for the same person on the
# same surface stack additively.
#
signals:
  assignee: 4.0             # GitHub issue assignee
  pr_author: 3.4            # PR author referencing item
  commit_author: 2.78        # Commit with item ID in branch/title/msg
  pr_reviewer: 2.25          # PR review submitted (excluding self)
  issue_comment: 1.14        # Comment on issue/PR (excluding bots)

# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# GATE WEIGHTS вЂ” Feature / Epic / Initiative status transitions
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
#
# Each status transition on Feature, Epic, or Initiative parents is a
# deliverable event the engine credits inside the iteration window.
# Weights split the parent's Job Size across its lifecycle, so prep
# work (LBC, decomposition, validation) is credited as it happens вЂ”
# not only at terminal Done. Weights MUST sum to 1.0 per item type.
# The gate event inherits the parent's contributors[] verbatim
# (per-item shares are unchanged by the gate split).
#
# Stories stay Done-only and flow through the regular backlog scan;
# they are never emitted as gate events.
#
gate_weights:
  Feature:                          # 7 transitions across 8 SAFe statuses
    "Funnelв†’Analyzing":         0.10  # LBC delivered
    "Analyzingв†’Backlog":        0.05  # Decomposed, AC defined
    "Backlogв†’Implementing":     0.05  # Sprint planning, breakdown
    "Implementingв†’Validating":  0.50  # Code merged (the bulk of work)
    "Validatingв†’Deploying":     0.15  # QA sign-off, acceptance
    "Deployingв†’Releasing":      0.05  # Deployed to prod
    "Releasingв†’Done":           0.10  # Release verified, hypothesis proven

  Epic:                             # 5 transitions across 6 portfolio statuses
    "Funnelв†’Reviewing":         0.05  # Triage
    "Reviewingв†’Analyzing":      0.10  # Accepted for LBC
    "Analyzingв†’Ready":          0.25  # LBC approved, MVP scope set
    "Readyв†’Implementing":       0.10  # Capacity allocated, kickoff
    "Implementingв†’Done":        0.50  # MVP delivered, hypothesis tested

  Initiative:                       # Same shape as Epic (portfolio level)
    "Funnelв†’Reviewing":         0.05
    "Reviewingв†’Analyzing":      0.10
    "Analyzingв†’Ready":          0.25
    "Readyв†’Implementing":       0.10
    "Implementingв†’Done":        0.50

# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# RULES
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
rules:
  - "All evidence signals contribute additively to contribution_score; no priority dominance"
  - "cw is per-item normalized: ОЈ cw[*, item] = 1.0 (engine invariant)"
  - "Manual /contribute directives stack as additional signals вЂ” they don't override auto-detection"
  - "ALL commits are delivery evidence вЂ” including governance (.edpa/, config/)"
  - "Stories at status=Done are credited; Feature/Epic/Initiative gate transitions are credited per gate_weight"
  - "Role labels (Owner/Key/Reviewer/Consulted) are derived at display time from signal types; never stored"

# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# PRINCIPLE: WORK = WORK
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# EDPA does not measure "code development" вЂ” it measures contribution
# to delivery. A PM who updates the backlog, plans iterations, and
# defines AC contributes via issue_comments + manual /contribute
# directives + assignee signals. A Dev who writes code contributes via
# commit_authors + pr_authors + assignee signals. Both flow through
# the same signal aggregation; the signal weights determine how each
# activity translates to cw share.
#
# Strategic-role bias correction (PM/BO/Arch under-weighting in Git):
# EDPA addresses this purely through calibration. signal_weights get
# tuned against ground truth that includes strategic-role
# contributions, so the calibrator naturally finds weights that match
# observed reality. Per-role signal multipliers may return as a
# calibration extension if small-pilot calibration shows persistent
# bias for strategic roles.

# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# CALIBRATION METADATA вЂ” populated by /edpa:calibrate
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
calibration:
  method: "MC random-sample + coordinate descent"
  monte_carlo:
    scenarios: 1000
    records: 31041
  ground_truth_records: 0   # synthetic baseline; re-run with real data after first PI
  mad_baseline: 0.0861
  mad_calibrated: 0.0805
  improvement_pct: 6.5
  calibrated_at: "2026-05-08T18:37:24Z"
  calibrated_by_version: "1.11.0"
  notes: |
    Synthetic Monte Carlo baseline (1000 scenarios,
    31041 records). Ground truth was generated
    procedurally from a model where signal counts probabilistically
    reflect each person's true cw share with role-based bias.
    Re-run /edpa:calibrate after first real PI close with team-confirmed
    cw records to derive a real-data baseline.
    Synthetic generator extends with 4 edge-case item flavors:
    pm_driven (PM owner without commits), pair_programmed (2 near-equal
    contributors), design_heavy (Arch consultant + dev impl + silent
    reviewer), minimal (single owner). 60%% normal Dirichlet flavor +
    40%% edge cases.

    Weights post-calibration rescaled to set max signal weight = 4.0
    (preserves cw ratios mod 2-decimal rounding; aligns auto weights
    with manual /contribute weight: convention).
